  "design_note": "Sub-context / target-sense / competitor labels are assigned PURELY from surface form / regex / gazetteer / disambiguating local context, independent of any SAE latent or model. Absorption presence/absence is a future-iteration EMPIRICAL finding, NOT baked into this data: the same labelled corpus equally supports the 'absorption is spelling-specific' null (uniform high parent-probe recall across homograph entities) and a positive homograph-absorption finding (suppressed-parent recall holes concentrated on high-strength homographs). The homograph_competitor family is the matched hard control that makes a suppressed parent visible. llm_corpus_sense_precision MEASURES the heuristic target-sense precision per hierarchy on a stratified sample; it does NOT relabel the corpus."
